African swine fever, Belgium
----------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 31 Dec 2018 from Dr. Jean-François Heymans, Director, Animal Health and Safety of Products of Animal Origin, Federal Agency for the Safety of the Food Chain (FASFC), Bruxelles, Belgium

Summary
Report type: Follow-up report No. 15
Date of start of the event: 9 Sep 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 13 Sep 2018
Report date: 31 Dec 2018
Date submitted to OIE: 31 Dec 2018
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 1985
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Virus de la peste porcine africaine
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (advanced), Necropsy
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (10)

[For the locations of each of the 10 new outbreaks, all situated within the declared "infected zone" in the southern part of the Belgian (Walloon) province Luxembourg, as well as for their start dates, dates of resolvement and the number of ASF-infected boars in each of them, subscribers are referred to the full report at the source URL. - Mod.AS].

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 10
Total animals affected
Species / Cases / Deaths/ Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Wild boar: Sus scrofa (Suidae) / 22 / 22 / 0 / 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Control measures
Measures applied: surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste; control of wildlife reservoirs; zoning
Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type: Sciensano (National laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Wild boar / real-time PCR / 24 Dec 2018 / Positive
Wild boar / real-time PCR / 27 Dec 2018 / Positive
Wild boar / real-time PCR / 28 Dec 2018 / Positive

Future Reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

